<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05036g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05036g">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05036g"> 36(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> secretarium</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Before he said Mass, Martin used always to make a long and devout preparation in a small inner sacristy, which was called the <mark>secretarium</mark>, because, unlike the outer sacristy, the faithful were not admitted to it. <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 90</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
